%N A394719 Numbers k such that |s(k) - 2*k|, where s(k) is the aliquot sum A001065(k), is a perfect number.
%C A394719 Includes all the perfect numbers (A000396).
%e A394719 84 is in this list, since |aliquot sum(84) - 2*84| = 28, which is a perfect number.
%t A394719 perfectQ[k_] := DivisorSigma[-1, k] == 2; q[k_] := perfectQ[Abs[DivisorSigma[1, k] - 3*k]]; Select[Range[10^6], q] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 30 2026 *)
%Y A394719 Cf. A000396, A001065, A033885.
%K A394719 nonn,new
%O A394719 1,1
